<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1550]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
: In some specimens, the sclerotized band on pygophore is produced into a denticle with a subapical black spot on pygophore. 
<taxonomicName box="[870,1002,1404,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpago">
<emphasis box="[870,1002,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">X. harpago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can at once be recognised by the truncate ventral median plate of the male genital capsule, a pointed and a hooked process of the aedeagal shaft in addition to other characters of the male genitalia among the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[550,672,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[550,672,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
